shire, England":"Dartmouth, Devon, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Preaux","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Lucien, Ulysse, Andre, Andree, Antoine, Gaston, Gracien, Pierre, Raoul.","Altered form of French   Brault  , itself a variant of   Braud  . This surname is also common among African Americans. Compare   Breau  ,   Breaud  ,   Bro  , and   Brow  .","History: The majority of the Breaux families of LA trace their origins to one Vincent Brault from La Chaussé in Vienne, who arrived in Acadia sometime before 1661 (see also   Brault  ). After the expulsion of the Acadians (1755–64), several of his descendants found their way to LA."],"variants":[{"name":"Brault","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Armand, Adelard, Alain, Andre, Gilles, Rosaire, Solange, Cecile, Emile, Francoise, Germaine, Girard.","French: variant of   Braud  . Its most common American French form is   Breaux  ; it was Americanized (Anglicized) as   Brow  ,   Broe  , and   Bro  . Compare   Breault  .","Altered form of American French   Breaux   back to its original form."]},{"name":"Breau","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Ulysse, Alcide, Antoine, Aurore, Girard, Leonide, Mederic, Ovila, Raoul, Yves, Yvon.","American French: variant of   Breaux  , and an altered form of its French cognates   Braud   and   Brault  .","French (<b>Bréau</b>): variant of <b>Breuil</b> (see   Dubreuil  )."]},{"name":"Breaud","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Urbain, Nemour.","American French: variant of   Breaux  .","In some cases possibly also French (<b>Bréaud</b>): variant of   Beraud  , a cognate of 1 above."]}]},{"name":"Pierre","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From New Testament Greek.  See  <b>Peter</b> ."],"variants":[{"name":"Peter","meanings":["form of the name of the best-known of all Christ's apostles, traditionally regarded as the founder of the Christian Church. The name derives, via Latin, from Greek <i>petros</i> ‘stone, rock’. This is used as a translation of the Aramaic byname <i>Cephas</i>, given to the apostle  Simon  son of Jona, to distinguish him from another of the same name (  Simon Zelotes ). ‘When Jesus beheld him, he said, Thou art Simon the son of Jona: thou shalt be called Cephas, which is by interpretation, A stone’ (John 1:42). According to Matthew 16:17–18, Christ says more explicitly, ‘Blessed art thou, Simon Bar-jona … thou art Peter, and upon this rock I will build my church’. The name has been in continuous use since the Middle Ages."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Pierre Preaux was born in 1175, in Merrivale, Devon, England as the son of Mrs. William Preaux. He had at least 1 daughter with F Preaux. He died in 1213, at the age of 38."},"et":{"1175–1213":"1175–1213","1175–Female":"1175–Surnud","1190–1300":"1190–1300","1155–Female":"1155–Surnud","1190":"1190","1213":"1213","1300":"1300","1155":"1155","1175":"1175","Merrivale, Devon, England":"Merrivale, Devon, England","Dartmouth, Devonshire, England":"Dartmouth, Devon, England"},"fi":{"1175–1213":"1175–1213","1175–Female":"1175–Kuollut","1190–1300":"1190–1300","1155–Female":"1155–Kuollut","1190":"1190","1213":"1213","1300":"1300","1155":"1155","1175":"1175","Merrivale, Devon, England":"Merrivale, Devon, England","Dartmouth, Devonshire, England":"Dartmouth, Devon, England"},"fr":{"1175–1213":"1175–1213","1175–Female":"1175–Décédée","1190–1300":"1190–1300","1155–Female":"1155–Décédée","1190":"1190","1213":"1213","1300":"1300","1155":"1155","1175":"1175","Merrivale, Devon, England":"Merrivale, Devon, Angleterre","Dartmouth, Devonshire, England":"Dartmouth, Devon, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Pierre Preaux est né en 1175, à Merrivale, Devon, Angleterre, fils de Mrs. William Preaux. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec F Preaux. Il est décédé en 1213, à l’âge de 38 ans